<item>
            <title>[LU-9803] Need to cast st_blksize to unsigned long for printf in directio.c</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9803</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Had a compilation fail due:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;directio.c: In function &apos;main&apos;:
directio.c:114:16: error: format &apos;%lu&apos; expects argument of type &apos;long unsigned int&apos;, but argument 4 has type &apos;__blksize_t&apos; [-Werror=format=]
                st.st_blksize);
                ^


&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the code&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;        printf(&quot;directio on %s for %dx%lu bytes \n&quot;, fname, blocks,
               st.st_blksize);


&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think we can get by with just casting that st_blksize to an unsigned long. I&apos;ll push a patch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
